text:
Inside Kate Middleton and Prince William’s life between family and royal engagements 
Kate Middleton is much busier now that her maternity leave has come to an end, as the Duchess of Cambridge is intensely involved in royal duties that are close to her heart. 
Another Hollywood couple has decided to go separate ways. Latest Rumors Tweet 
Kate Middleton is much busier now that her maternity leave has come to an end, as the Duchess of Cambridge is intensely involved in royal duties that are close to her heart. 
The royal mother-of-two is juggling royal engagements and family life, as she has her hands full with two young children, Princess Charlotte, 4 months, and Prince George, 2. 
Her husband Prince William, who started his work as an East Anglian Air Ambulance pilot back in July, is too occupied, as the Duke of Cambridge is also dividing his time between his family, his job and royal engagaments. 
Kate recently carried out two royal engagament solo, one at the Anna Freud Centre almost two weeks ago, offering support to the children’s mental health treatment charity, and another one last week at HMP Send in Surrey, where she met inmates struggling with addictions. 
A royal source talked with People about the royal couple’s life between Norfolk and London. 
“They are very much between the two,” the source told the magazine. “They spent a large part of the summer up at Anmer, but now there is many engagements traveling to and from London. They’ll be very much spending time in London as well.” 
Next month, Duchess Kate will most likey join her husband, the Duke of Cambridge, in welcoming China’s president Xi Jinping and his wife Peng Liyuan, and the royal might wear a tiara at the banquet, considering the royal protocol. Also, Kate, William and Harry are set to attend the world premiere of the latest Bond movie in October. Spread the rumor
